CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 25, 1961, pg. 9, reads: "Symposium Participants - Panelists at last Sunday's fair housing discussion at the Loendi Club included (left to right) Atty. Eric Springer, Louis Mason, deputy director of the Mayor's Committee on Human Relations; Roland Sawyer, Loendi Club president and housing consultant for the United Steelworkers of America; P. L. Prattis, Courier editor and symposium moderator; Arthur Swotzer, president of the Home Builders Association; Carl Nickel, past president of the Home Builders, and Roland Catarinella, prominent Pittsburgh builder and realtor. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Men seated around table, from left: Eric Springer, Louis Mason, Roland Sawyer, P. L. Prattis, Arthur Swotzer, Carl Nickel, and Roland Catarinella, for symposium on fair housing, Loendi Club
